Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.94,0:03:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We are scheduled for today.\NIt's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.21,0:03:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the first break will be at 2 to 11.30.\NNow, in the universal room, which is the last room to the left over here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.71,0:03:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,there is refreshments for you on both breaks.\NThen the lunch hour will be from 12 to 2 o'clock
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can leave if you want to have lunch.\NWe'll resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.46,0:04:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after the second break is at 3.15,\Nand that's when we have our question and answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have any questions that you would like to ask Dr. at that time,\Nwe'll form two lines and we'll sign books at that time also
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.81,0:04:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can come up and ask any questions.\NAnd the good news is that we have a new website that's ready to be up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.64,0:04:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been working on it.\NRobert's been working on it diligently for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.12,0:04:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you'd like to take a peek at it, it's Dr. Paul Kempf.\NDr. Hawkins.info.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.29,0:04:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to take a quick peek at it.\NWe're going to have little clips of some of the seminars in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.00,0:04:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins.info.\NDr. Hawkins.info.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.26,0:04:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to take a peek, we're going to have some little cuts out of seminars.\NDoes that mean I'm, does that qualify me as a blogger?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.26,0:04:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope not.\NDoes that make me a blogger?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.38,0:05:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You are. You are one.\NGet ready to be blogged, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.91,0:05:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You ain't seen no blogging until you see my blogging.\NThat's humility for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.82,0:05:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What a divine blessing to be here.\NI don't know what we're talking about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.30,0:05:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I made a diagram.\NOh yes, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.79,0:05:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we all start off.\NThe same way that we start off in the end of the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:06:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And to save all that time of having to listen through all that.\NYou live your life in a contemplative style.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.37,0:06:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In a contemplative style, you're not commenting on everything all the time.\NYou're not taking a positionality about it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.86,0:06:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just witnessing it.\NThe witness is already detached from the participant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.93,0:06:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the leading edge of the ego.\NThe exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.69,0:06:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer.\NHe's not content with just witnessing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to get involved.\NAnd give you its opinion, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.91,0:06:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the world going to do without?\NAnyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.61,0:06:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A contemplative lifestyle, if you do it habitually,\Nit will come out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.44,0:07:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The witnessing that all phenomena are occurring spontaneously.\NAs a consequence of that which they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.81,0:07:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And for no other reason.\NYou see that things are emerging, evolving, and appearing as they appear spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.13,0:07:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,By contemplation and witnessing then, you've shut off the mind.\NAnd without the mind, you don't see any cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.98,0:07:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a mentalization you project.\NSo, if through humility, you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.88,0:07:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear God, I don't know what anything means anyway.\NI would like to be the witness of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.88,0:08:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you witness creation.\NAnd you witness creation, doing whatever creation is, how it's evolving at this unfoldingness over what the world calls time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.88,0:08:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sequentially.\NYou realize that all phenomena are being what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.48,0:08:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Expressing their essence by which what the world calls evolution occurs.\NAnd therefore, it throws it on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.31,0:08:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of nowhere, not out of thinkingness.\NThat creation and evolution are the one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.72,0:08:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That what you're seeing is evolution, which is creation in 3D.\NThe linear expression of evolution then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.13,0:08:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The linear which you can witness in the physical domain.\NThis is very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.54,0:09:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?\NAnybody have a problem with evolution and creation are one and the same thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.92,0:09:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, there's no conflict.\NNo conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.11,0:09:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No conflict.\NSo, non-duality means you withdraw from the participant experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.51,0:09:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience or edge of the ego.\NAnd instead, you withdraw to the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.74,0:09:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You withdraw from thinkingness.\NThinkingness comes to your aid when you want it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.04,0:09:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not supposed to be at the effect of thinkingness.\NThat it allows you peace when it wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.60,0:09:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's supposed to be the other way.\NYou think when you decide to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.84,0:09:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When there's some purpose or benefit.\NSomething that you have to go into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:09:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And left brain it.\NSequentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.84,0:10:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is wearisome, frankly.\NWhy anybody prizes the body and the mind is beyond me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.04,0:10:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But they do so.\NBoth are wearisome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.08,0:10:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NHowever, without a body you can't walk around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.21,0:10:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can see it does serve a useful purpose.\NWe're talking about overcoming obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.00,0:10:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today.\NThat's the name of the.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.00,0:10:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I seldom pay attention to the title of the lecture.\NBut I did notice it was overcoming obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Overcoming obstacles.\NAnd the human condition is certainly full of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.17,0:10:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Buddha said transcend the identification of the linear.\NBecause this is a world of considerable discomfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.27,0:11:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWhich we witness in today's news.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.44,0:11:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThe tragic events which sweep across the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.91,0:11:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In one place or another almost continuously throughout all of history.\NEarthquake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.20,0:11:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Flood.\NLightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.59,0:11:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsunamis.\NHurricanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.59,0:11:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're frightening.\NSame time they're exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.03,0:11:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the same time they allow us the full expression of our own karmic potential.\NWe always watch the weather news at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.39,0:11:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The storm stories.\NStorm stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:12:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice that the survivors of catastrophes in relating it subsequently almost all.\NAlmost every single one of them remarked about how they prayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one of the quickest ways to God is to face sudden death.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.51,0:12:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Atheism goes just like that.\NAnd it's possible through surrender to face anything with great equanimity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.53,0:12:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk right into the hail of bullets and either you die or you don't die.\NWhich is surrender to the will of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.12,0:12:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is different than nihilism.\NIt's different than denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.89,0:12:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's different than skepticism let's say.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.37,0:12:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I thought today also the obstacles are the limitations of the mind.\NAnd skepticism has sort of showed up on the radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.48,0:13:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I thought we have a similar goal in mind with skepticism.\NSkepticism arose in ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The philosophy of ancient Greece.\NThe followers of Pyro.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.30,0:13:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,P-R-R-Y-H-O I think is the spelling.\NSkeptikos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Greek word is skeptikos.\NAnd the philosophy of the skeptic was that truth is not knowable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.50,0:13:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not knowable.\NWhich is exactly what we say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.82,0:13:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind in and of itself is unable to discern truth from falsehood.\NTherefore, you would think skepticism would be a great fan of ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.20,0:13:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it seems to be antagonized by us.\NMainly because, you know, consciousness research verifies the validity of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.67,0:13:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, which is antagonistic to the skeptic.\NSo, of course, the problem with the skeptic is if truth is unknowable,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.44,0:14:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it means that there is no value to their speech.\NBecause their speech is also there expressing ignorance, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.96,0:14:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the skeptic is hung in his own petard.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.69,0:14:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If knowledge is not knowable, then what are they blabbering about?\NAnyway, we did write a little essay on skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.82,0:14:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that sort of has come up in the world of bloggers.\NI am now a fellow blogger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.05,0:14:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they better watch out.\NSuffer from bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.84,0:14:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NMuch of bloggerism, you know, is services.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.84,0:14:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great purpose.\NIt provides information, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.84,0:14:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's what I call the vanity sites, you know.\NMy turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.00,0:15:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill's corn.\NBill tells you what he thinks about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.24,0:15:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, skepticism calibrates about 160.\NNow, why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.27,0:15:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a low.\NIn as much as ostensibly, it supposedly is seeking the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.95,0:15:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it is very close to nihilism.\NNihilism calibrates at 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.95,0:15:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It is also very close to anarchy because it denies the authenticity of all authority.\NAnd therefore skepticism is by its nature atheistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.03,0:15:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.20,0:15:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't carry it too far.\NThe good side of skepticism is that it has revealed outrageous frauds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.20,0:15:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Outrageous frauds.\NAnd therefore I'm an enthusiast to skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.20,0:15:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NUh, with a sharp eye on its downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.38,0:16:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However, when you study skepticism, you end up skeptical of scepticism.\NI do not think that skepticism is going to lead us to God or to truth or the salvation of mankind, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.38,0:16:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, every new development in mankind's history brings the skeptics out of the woodwork.\NI was a little worried that they weren't coming around after I published truth versus nihilism.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.38,0:16:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, good God.\NNot even worth the skeptics attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.38,0:16:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But now my ego is reinflated.\NI am happy to be under attack by the skeptics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.38,0:16:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I'm somebody.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.71,0:16:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm somebody.\NSo I have my sympathy is with what I think is their ostensible purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.12,0:16:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it is not.\NIt is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not.\NIt is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.79,0:16:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not.\NIt is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.52,0:16:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not.\NIt is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.60,0:16:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not.\NIt is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not.\NIt is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.60,0:16:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm an somebody, I'm not somebody, I have a purpose.\NHowever, the methodology, etc., it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.26,0:17:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like the message, you attack the messengers.\NSo also in blogger land we've had ad hominem attacks on yours truly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.26,0:17:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thank thee, Lord, that I do not have an unpaid parking ticket.\NClean as the whistle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.66,0:17:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No parking tickets.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.63,0:17:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\Nconfrontational. There's a caveat in the front of the book, Truth vs. Fault. The caveat tells you that it's confrontational.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.75,0:17:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not prepared for it, don't read any further.\NSome people ignored the caveat, obviously. I thought we would do some, a couple of things, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.33,0:17:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the other thing they question, of course, is kinesiology. So I said before I wrote this,\Nyou'll get politically motivated attacks, which they all are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.66,0:18:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you'll get people that are very anti-God, they all are, and then you get the critics of kinesiology, because\Nnot a single
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.53,0:18:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,critic has addressed the main premises or the main conclusions or anything important in the book, so they didn't comprehend that at all.\NSo nobody has addressed that at all. They only go for the peripheral issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.05,0:18:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So the skeptic,\Nyou know, questions kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.60,0:18:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I taught kinesiology,\Nyou know, kinesiology was new on the radar 30 years ago. It's old hat now. Everybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.89,0:18:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,done all the tricks to try and prove it and disprove it, and\Nthere's many very excellent
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,DVDs out there by professionals in kinesiology\Nwho know a great deal about it. I know practically nothing about it. I just know yes or no, that's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.51,0:18:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's many tricks you can do. You can go like this, and they go weak, and then you go like this, and they go hot,\Nand then you go like this, and they go strong, and you go this, and they go weak, so
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.64,0:19:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes me dizzy, and\NPat Flanagan used to be an expert showing on that, and so if you're really interested in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.94,0:19:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm only interested in it that it serves a\Npedagogical function
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.27,0:19:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because it allows us how to\Nmove from the Newtonian paradigm of science
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.03,0:19:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,into the nonlinear domain. It gives us the only trail I know of from the linear to the nonlinear.\NTherefore, I thought it served a pedagogical technique, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But if your findings come up to support what people don't want to hear about, then they suddenly hate kinesiology,\Nwhich is the only other possible attack they can have on it, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.11,0:19:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So I used to give lectures all over the country, all the world in fact, and\Nyou know, the results were consistent in every single country.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.90,0:20:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The mistake I made in meoculpa\Nthe error, the omission, was in power versus force. You know, I'll tell you how it developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.02,0:20:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw kinesiology with John Diamond and did a workshop with him, and then I\Nstarted giving lectures on it because I had a huge clinic, you see, and we used holistic
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,practices. We thought kinesiology would lead us maybe to\Nunsuspected causes of mental disorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.85,0:20:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So I added that to, you know, we did all kinds of things.\NThey were non-traditional and had tremendous recoveries in hopeless cases. The clinic specialized in hopeless cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We had the largest practice in the country.\NPeople came from all over the world because we've got recoveries where nobody else could, and it's because we weren't just limited to the Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.90,0:20:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional science.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.43,0:20:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,medicine has always been town versus gown. The town\Nare the doctors that are out there, and the gown
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.76,0:21:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is the academics, who live in a much more restrained\Nworld of provability.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.80,0:21:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The experienced clinician can get recoveries where the academics can't, so our usual patient\Nhad been to all the universities, seen all the specialists, and were given up as hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.78,0:21:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we specialized in the hopeless.\NSo we looked for everything that could be helpful on kinesiology was one of the things we researched.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.18,0:21:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So I began teaching it. So\Nwhen we started teaching it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.99,0:21:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to give a class.\NSo in the clinic back there,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.58,0:21:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we had A Course in Miracles students\Nand all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.72,0:21:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I grabbed a couple of people\Nand I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,there's one traditional test.\NIf you take an ordinary person
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.54,0:21:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and they look at fluorescent lights,\Nthey go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.91,0:21:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hold sweet and low\Nwhere there's solar plexus,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.17,0:21:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they go weak.\NSo I grabbed a couple of people
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.06,0:21:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said, okay,\Nwell, let's try this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.84,0:22:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So we did the fluorescent thing\Nand they didn't go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.17,0:22:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we tried the sweet and low,\Nthey didn't go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.30,0:22:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, God,\Nthey're going to make
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.13,0:22:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,lousy test subjects, I tell you.\NBut the curiosity was,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.45,0:22:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,how come they didn't?\NThen we discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.94,0:22:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it had something to do\Nwith A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.46,0:22:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So we got some new students\Nwho were just starting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.79,0:22:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A Course in Miracles\Nand I tested them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.38,0:22:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They went weak\Nwith fluorescent lights
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.64,0:22:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and sweet and low.\NAnd we tested them serially.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.75,0:22:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And about the time\Nthey got to less than 75,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.52,0:22:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,80 around in there,\Nsuddenly fluorescent lights
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.56,0:22:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,did not make them go weak,\Nnor did sweet and low
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.10,0:22:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,nor any other local stimulus\Nmake them go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.68,0:22:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha.\NSo, anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.25,0:22:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when I wrote Power Versus Force\Nand we did a video on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.46,0:22:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the video is still,\Nisn't there one,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.48,0:22:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a demonstration of Power Versus Force\Non kinesiology?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.53,0:23:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWell, all the people I knew
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.11,0:23:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and hung out with\Nall calibrated over,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.85,0:23:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,200, you know what I'm saying?\NSo we thought that kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.89,0:23:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,would be useful for everyone.\NThen we later discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.47,0:23:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can't use it\Nbelow 200
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.15,0:23:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the integrity\Nof the question
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.47,0:23:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,also has to be 200.\NSo I didn't put that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.60,0:23:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in Power Versus Force\Nand I must have created
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.23,0:23:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the illusion that anybody,\Nanywhere can do it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.32,0:23:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,under any circumstance,\Nwhich is not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's later corrected\Nin subsequent books.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.80,0:23:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But so I take responsibility\Nthat we did not know it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.39,0:23:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time.\NAnd when we did the video
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.10,0:23:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,on Power Versus Force\Ndemonstrating the kinesiologic test,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.50,0:23:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we grabbed everybody\Nthat came along
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.71,0:23:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were all\Nintegrous people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.19,0:23:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So of course it worked\Nfor 100% of those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.00,0:23:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it probably worked\Nfor 100% of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.93,0:23:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in this crowd, you know,\Nbecause you wouldn't be here
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.69,0:23:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,if you were under 200,\NI don't suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.44,0:24:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the error was\NI thought everybody could do it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.09,0:24:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I misled the public\Nby, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.98,0:24:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by, you know,\Nomission.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.20,0:24:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I just didn't know it.\NSo therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.98,0:24:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology,\Nconsciousness research,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.14,0:24:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera,\Nare evolving,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.27,0:24:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Nand they're evolving.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.83,0:24:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They're evolving.\NSo I thought we'd do
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.94,0:24:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a brief demonstration\Nthis morning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.44,0:24:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for those of you\Nwho never heard
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.22,0:24:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,one of my wonderful lectures\Non kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.57,0:24:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do the whole thing\Nin about two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.20,0:24:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll take two minutes.\NYou want to participate?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.78,0:24:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NUnder threat, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.97,0:24:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Come over here.\NYou're a calcitrant lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.36,0:24:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NStand here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.52,0:24:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,\Nall right,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.06,0:24:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if the crowd\Ncan see this or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.04,0:24:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but I,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.82,0:24:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,all you have to do\Nis read the book
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.26,0:24:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Behavioral Kinesiology\Nby John Diamond
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.73,0:25:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and it tells you\Nall you need to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.45,0:25:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you see?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.28,0:25:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right,\NI just want you to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.04,0:25:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to look\Nat the top diagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.45,0:25:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.13,0:25:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to look.\NI want you to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.67,0:25:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to look.\NI want you to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.73,0:25:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to look.\NI want you to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.86,0:25:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to look.\NJust at the lower diagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.36,0:25:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NSo you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.40,0:25:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no psychological suggestion.\NI'm not selling her any program.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.68,0:25:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not to prove anything.\NYou understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.53,0:25:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a physiologic response\Nto a stimulus.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.66,0:25:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.33,0:25:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hold something in mind.\NI'm going to hold something in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.28,0:25:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNow resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.91,0:25:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay,\NI'm going to hold something else in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.75,0:25:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NLincoln at first
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.60,0:25:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and Bin Laden second.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.99,0:25:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.50,0:25:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Nit's,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.79,0:25:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology is so simple.\NI don't see anything to argue about,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.01,0:25:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?\NIt's all like,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.61,0:26:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a retard can do it,\Nyou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.56,0:26:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NI don't know what's in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.95,0:26:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but it says do not swallow.\NSo anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.08,0:26:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NJust look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.91,0:26:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just please,\Njust look at the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.59,0:26:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus and concentrate on the bottle.\NNow resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.14,0:26:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.66,0:26:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now just,\Njust focus on the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.96,0:26:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at the bottle.\NNow resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.14,0:26:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on this bottle.\NNo, no, no, no,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.94,0:26:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottle.\NNot on the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.25,0:26:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NNot the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.66,0:26:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on the content of the bottle.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.77,0:26:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.31,0:26:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it again.\NFocus on this bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.94,0:27:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on this bottle.\NThe bottles are okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.53,0:27:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the bottles are okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.90,0:27:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in them?\NOne is Miracle Girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.97,0:27:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which miracles strong and the other is a poison that kills bugs and ants and stuff.\NSo she doesn't know what it's in it because I was sprung this as a surprise there this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.01,0:27:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you all want to do it at once,\Nwe can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.57,0:27:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to take out five minutes?\NI'll show you how we used to do it in the big city.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.04,0:28:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The person next to you,\Nyou decide who's going to be a one and who's going to be a two.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.69,0:28:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I got to do.\NOne, two, one, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.57,0:28:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Just choose who's one, who's two.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.82,0:28:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.78,0:28:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up, stand up.\NOnes and twos face each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.23,0:28:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ones and twos face each other.\NI don't, I don't want to mix them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.63,0:28:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOnes and twos.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.56,0:28:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have to have silence.\NWe have to silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.86,0:28:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, okay.\NThe, the, the, what we're trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.34,0:28:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is, uh, um, for the sake of the highest good, discover truth.\NSo that has to be the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.67,0:28:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.80,0:28:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Number one is the doctor.\NNumber two is the test subject who puts their arm out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.49,0:28:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Who put out numbers two, put out your test subject.\NEverybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.77,0:28:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Number two is put out your arm.\NNumber one's, uh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.83,0:29:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Number twos.\NI also, I want you to all look at what's in this bottle,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.49,0:29:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is in my hand.\NThis green powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.04,0:29:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNumber twos, look at the powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.99,0:29:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NDoctors number one, press down on their arm and say, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.50,0:29:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they resist?\NEverybody goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.55,0:29:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNow, occasionally a person will give you a paradoxical answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.15,0:29:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they'll give you a paradoxical answer.\NNow, did anybody go weak on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.52,0:29:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we can fix that right away.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.00,0:29:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you went weak, I want you to do the following thing.\NUh, I got a microphone on.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.09,0:29:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how I can do this.\NYou pound down the upper breastbone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.52,0:30:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You go, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.73,0:30:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you do, you think of somebody you love when you do that.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.14,0:30:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And any time you say, I surrender my life to God.\NYou don't have to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.01,0:30:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.18,0:30:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, those that went weak before, let's retest them.\NTeams, retest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.35,0:30:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, okay.\NThose that went weak before, test subjects, focus on the content of this bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.10,0:30:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at the bottle.\NDon't think anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.08,0:30:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.89,0:30:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctors say resist and press down on their arm with two fingers.\NHow do we do this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.09,0:30:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAnybody that didn't get fixed by the thymus thump, uh, has to stay after class and we'll work with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.21,0:31:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll work with you.\NNo, it's because, um, anybody who's done acupuncture and all knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.17,0:31:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's been listening to certain kind of music within the last half hour, uh, and various things like that will make you go weak for a period of time.\NAlso various physical conditions or medications you're taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.82,0:31:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, uh, but the majority of people, most of the time it's going to work.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.21,0:31:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, now what's the other one?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.07,0:31:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NLet's do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.09,0:31:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This time we want number twos to look at the contents of this bottle.\NLook, just look at the contents of this, uh, focus on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.11,0:31:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NDoctors, uh, tell them to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.01,0:31:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Press down with two fingers, two fingers, resist, resist, resist.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.70,0:31:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you can see this diagram from the floor.\NUh, you could do it again with a curved smile on top and a curved smile on the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.76,0:32:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I like the curve smile because there's no content to it.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.35,0:32:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you want it, we can switch ones and twos switch number two, you're going to be the patient.\NNumber one, you're going to be the doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.90,0:32:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, sorry.\NNumber two, you're going to be the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.53,0:32:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, you can tell them that they should close their eyes during this, because otherwise anything could have, the one who's being tested should be the doctor.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.77,0:32:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Susan, who's an expert at, probably the world's expert, says also close your eyes.\NUh, she can't, they can't look at this and close their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.77,0:32:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, just look at this to close your eyes, get the energy of it.\NOkay, doctors, press down with two fingers and say resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.05,0:32:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly, briefly, resist.\NHa, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.76,0:32:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that, that's just the experience of it.\NWe can all sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.96,0:33:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what I just want you to notice, it's very simple.\NIt's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.42,0:33:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so out there in blogger land, uh, out there in blogger land, of course, there's people that demean kinesiology, etc.\NAnd, uh, every single one of them calibrates at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.50,0:33:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The skeptics dictionary calibrates at 160.\NThe author of the skeptics website calibrates at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.53,0:33:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the references that, uh.\NAnd demean, kinesiology, all, all calibrate at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.73,0:33:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So 160 is the level of skepticism, skepticism.\NAnd the skeptic is, uh, why it's so low, as I said, it has to do with nihilism, really
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.43,0:33:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with the negation of truth.\NOf course, the real problem is the narcissistic ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.93,0:34:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NThe narcissistic ego, uh, feels extremely threatened that there is such a thing as absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.80,0:34:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, uh, and divinity.\NBecause the narcissistic ego, uh, to itself is divinity, and therefore God would be the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.71,0:34:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimate hated rival.\NAnd you see, therefore, the criticisms are, uh, pretty polemic, pretty polemic, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.46,0:34:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it threatens the, it threatens the narcissistic ego, uh, so, see if a person's\Nreally interested in inquiry, they ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.55,0:34:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NThey ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.94,0:34:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They ask a question.\NThey ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.32,0:34:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How come this or that?\NOf course, most, a lot of the questions are, you know, have to do with the irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.65,0:34:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How come a hippopotamus calibrates more than a toad or something?\NHaving nothing to do with getting to God, but, uh, you know, the design of the books
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.96,0:35:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has the intention of enlightenment, so it's only to, to provide some kind of a, uh, teaching,\Nuh, technique, method that just confirms God.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.32,0:35:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NThat just confirms, gives an additional confirm...confirmation, because of the modern mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.65,0:35:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The, uh, in ancient times, uh, science did not dominate, nor did Newtonian paradigm of,\Nuh, provability and causability, so in the old days faith was all that was, uh, sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.15,0:35:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NThe modern mind, uh, takes faith, but with a grain of salt, so the idea of kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.28,0:35:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as a pedagogical technique...\Nis it adds an affirmation to truth that is comprehensible and meaningful
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.82,0:35:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to the modern intellectual scientific mind, understand?\NSo it's just a pedagogical technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.40,0:36:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I pointed out in my response to that blogger, give him a blog, baby.\NThese are not textbooks on kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.67,0:36:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, pick up John Diamond or somebody else.\NSo anyway, I just thought I'd mention that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.86,0:36:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I mentioned it was because somebody sent me a book on bloggers,\Nand it said the first negative blog that comes up about you, you better answer it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.23,0:36:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise it's going to be copied all over the Internet.\NSo ordinarily I would have just ignored it and let it go away by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.90,0:36:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I decided it's better to do what we've got to do.\NThere's a certain...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.32,0:36:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,misunderstanding of spirituality that thinks it has to do with passivity.\NPassivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.73,0:36:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people think you should be of a certain political persuasion\Nand also a pacifist.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.17,0:36:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Passivity.\NAs we pointed out, truth versus falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.46,0:37:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Passivity actually calibrates below 200.\NNo, spiritual truth means to stand for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.86,0:37:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To stand for the truth.\NPassivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.44,0:37:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Passivity, then, is encouraging fallacy, is it not?\NTo not speak back to falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.98,0:37:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To not stand up for truth.\NWe noticed that standing up for truth cost Socrates his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.82,0:37:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It cost Jesus Christ his life.\NIt cost all the apostles.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.80,0:37:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All the apostles ended up in disasters.\NAny one of them could have survived by merely refuting
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.44,0:37:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth.\NRefuting the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.07,0:37:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou have to stand for the truth and I think the best way to do it is to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.32,0:37:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,To explain.\NTherefore I wrote an essay on skepticism and I wrote an essay on kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.73,0:38:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which will be out there in bloggerland maybe.\NAnd it's just that because you want to recontextualize it so that it's more comprehensible and then
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.65,0:38:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what they do about it is their own karmic problem.\NAll right, so is there any more questions about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.65,0:38:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There was also a misquote.\NThey don't mind misquoting you all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.09,0:38:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That I lost my thumb in an accident.\NI did not lose my thumb in an accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.84,0:38:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,nor did I state that I,\NI never stated that I lost my thumb in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.71,0:38:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I said in the universe, no accident is possible\Nbecause everything is in divine order.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.94,0:38:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe is infinite, infinite.\NSo how can anything occur outside of the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.17,0:38:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is in divine order.\NNot long ago, four of us met,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.84,0:38:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think in the northwest someplace at a convention,\Nfour of us of this group,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.94,0:39:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all four of us are missing a thumb.\NIn fact, there's another missing thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.42,0:39:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Four of us missing thumbs.\NYou think that's by accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.96,0:39:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why have four of us that show up at the same place\Nall missing the same thumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.28,0:39:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice in my writings I say,\Nswear no.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.01,0:39:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Swear no oaths.\NOr let the words be my fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.75,0:39:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, it came out of the Bible,\Nswearing oaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.76,0:39:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know where it came from.\NI just knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.42,0:39:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Swear no oaths because you don't know\Nin what lifetime you're going to pay it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.65,0:39:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So all four of us paid it off.\NWe were members 300 years ago in the same brotherhood
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.67,0:39:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all swore and did the blood thumb deal.\NAnd if we,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.82,0:39:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,if we break this vow,\Nmay so and so happen to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.96,0:39:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and it did.\NSo it was not by accident at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.96,0:40:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It was,\Nand when all four of us came together,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.61,0:40:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nwe did some past life research.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.78,0:40:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We all belonged to the same organization\Nand the same group.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.51,0:40:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all left it\Nand may the reverse be our fate
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.17,0:40:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,was the price we paid.\NSo losing the thumb,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.76,0:40:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,was not accidental.\NThat's confusing it with intentional.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.51,0:40:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think it's not intentional,\Nthat doesn't mean it's accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.51,0:40:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It just means it's not intentional.\NSo losing the thumb was not intentional consciously,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.51,0:40:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but fate just had its moment.\NBoom, like that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.51,0:40:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Quicker than a wink.\NQuicker than a wink.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.51,0:40:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you only need this one to hitchhike,\Nso it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.51,0:40:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent many years,\NI hitchhiked to school every day for years,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.26,0:40:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,out in the cold and snow.\NWisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.88,0:40:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course then I was also maligned\Nthat there was one commentary,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.88,0:40:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I'll finish with the Bloggerland.\NIt said,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.38,0:41:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,\Nhe grew up in the Midwest
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.88,0:41:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and was in World War II.\NSo that explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.55,0:41:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he can't help it.\NHe grew up in the Midwest
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.80,0:41:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and was in World War II.\NAnd went to church as a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.30,0:41:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, I mean,\Nwhat can you expect from a guy like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.44,0:41:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought I'd share those little biographical things.\NWell, we live in a current world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.44,0:41:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in which Bloggerland is a reality,\Nand therefore it's just something
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.44,0:41:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we have learned to live with, you know.\NI don't know how to work a computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.44,0:41:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't want to.\NI once came across the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.69,0:41:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was covering a clinic\Nin Cottonwood
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.69,0:41:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,where the doctor was sick,\Nand they gave me this office.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.69,0:41:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This was many years ago,\Nand here sat this thing I'd heard about
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.69,0:41:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,called the computer.\NAnd I examined it all over,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.69,0:41:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I looked at it,\Nand I couldn't find an on or off switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.51,0:42:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at the plug.\NI examined it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.51,0:42:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no on or off switch on that.\NThe next week I came back,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.61,0:42:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,same office.\NI examined it all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.61,0:42:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no on or off switch.\NThat was the end of my interest in computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.03,0:42:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the end of my romance with computers.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.03,0:42:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's,\Nhow many people here are new, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.78,0:42:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.78,0:42:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this again,\Nbecause for the sake of the new,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.78,0:42:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to cover the basics.\NThe basics are in the written material.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.78,0:42:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore,\Nwe don't spend a lot of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.78,0:42:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But we do cover the basics enough\Nfor somebody who hasn't been here before
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.78,0:42:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or is a guest\Nto give them some comprehension
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.78,0:42:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and overall contextualization, Betty.\NBetty.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.96,0:42:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Boop.\NWay ahead of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.51,0:42:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe map of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.78,0:43:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the other thing is,\Npeople accuse you of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.78,0:43:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because they're so positionalized,\Nthey can't imagine that somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.78,0:43:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,could not come from a non-positionality\Nlooking for some kind of gain, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.78,0:43:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They project onto you what they do themselves.\NYou'll notice that you don't have any stake
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.80,0:43:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in what the answer's going to be.\NSo to get a correct answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.80,0:43:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't have any stake in it.\NTherefore, I'll say,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.80,0:43:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all,\Nask for the arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.80,0:43:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.\NNumber one, get permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.03,0:43:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NYou remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.15,0:43:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in some of the lectures,\Nwe got nos, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.15,0:43:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We got nos.\NAnd sometimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.15,0:43:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because of people that were in the group,\Nwe got the no at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.15,0:43:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway,\Nyou can get a no.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.15,0:43:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have to position\Nwhat you want to address
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.15,0:43:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as a statement,\Nnot a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.15,0:43:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A statement.\NOld Rover is still
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.23,0:44:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,something or other.\NAnd then you quickly press down,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.40,0:44:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a very quick response.\NYou can ask for the,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.40,0:44:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good.\NSo the right way to do it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.40,0:44:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.48,0:44:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of the highest good,\NI have permission to calibrate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.48,0:44:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd so and so calibrates over 200, 300, 400,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.48,0:44:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever, until the arm goes weak.\NNow, you have no vested interest
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.48,0:44:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in that answer,\Nhaving turned it over
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.48,0:44:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to the highest good,\Nand avoiding, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.73,0:44:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to beg the question.\NSo people who are integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.01,0:44:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and who follow the right technique,\Nthen again,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.01,0:44:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a matter of experience.\NNow, kinesiology is not the only way
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.03,0:44:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth from falsehood,\Nphysiologically.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.13,0:44:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a whole raft of them,\Nthe whole raft of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.59,0:44:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Pupillary response,\Nblood pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.59,0:45:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,breathing,\Nvasomotor response,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.59,0:45:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,idiomotor response,\Nacupuncture balance,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.59,0:45:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,brain physiology.\NThere's a million ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.59,0:45:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are very good at it.\NThey just stand up,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.59,0:45:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and truth makes them fall forward,\Nand falsehood makes them fall backward.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.59,0:45:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use your whole body like a pendulum.\NOf course, dowsers do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.80,0:45:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember going across the border\Ninto Northern Ireland
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.80,0:45:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,many years ago\Nwhen there was conflict,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.90,0:45:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you crossed the border\Ninto Northern Ireland,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.90,0:45:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the police there patted you down,\Nand they looked you in the eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.90,0:45:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,closely at your pupil,\Nand they said,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.90,0:45:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are you carrying a gun?\NThey watched your pupil response.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.03,0:45:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, being a doctor,\NI said, that's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.03,0:45:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're watching the pupil?\NHe says, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.03,0:45:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch for a flare of the pupil\Nwhen the guy lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.09,0:45:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, of course,\Nthe lie detector is set up
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.09,0:45:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to do all these things.\NBody language,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.09,0:46:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,facial expression,\Nvoice analysis is common.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.09,0:46:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A guy gives a lecture,\Nand the voice analyst says
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.09,0:46:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,he was lying on this sentence,\Nhe was lying on this sentence,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.09,0:46:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,lying on this sentence.\NThere's many ways to verify it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.09,0:46:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology is so quick.\NI just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.09,0:46:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think about,\NI think so-and-so has a good idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.09,0:46:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,resist.\NThat takes less than about 30 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.09,0:46:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I can't set up\Na whole brainwave machine
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.09,0:46:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and do all that crazy stuff\Nfor a voice analysis machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.09,0:46:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, kinesiology is not,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.09,0:46:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just one of many,\Nbut it's practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.09,0:46:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's practical.\NSo, I thought I'd mention that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.09,0:46:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, we'll go back
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.57,0:46:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to the map of consciousness,\Nwhich is pretty much known worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.57,0:46:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in just about every language\Nin the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.57,0:46:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nwe use kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.61,0:46:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop a war, you know.\NIt was,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.80,0:46:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a near ballistic missile war,\Nthe verge of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.80,0:47:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.90,0:47:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan and I got\Ntracked halfway across the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.90,0:47:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nwith all the top officials
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.90,0:47:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of the government\Nin front of all the officials,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.90,0:47:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who are very wise men,\Nthank God,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.90,0:47:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we analyzed every single move\Non this side
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.90,0:47:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and every single response\Non that side.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.90,0:47:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we came up\Nwith a resolution
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.90,0:47:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to support the person's\Npolitical power,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.90,0:47:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in which case\Nhe will drop military power.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.90,0:47:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Within 72 hours,\Nthe headlines
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.28,0:47:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,were a piece.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.28,0:47:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it's pragmatic value.\NIt allows you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.28,0:47:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to access information\Nthat's not available
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.28,0:47:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,by any ordinary means.\NA great deal
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.28,0:47:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the stuff\Nthat we appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.36,0:47:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that appears\Nin Truth Versus Falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.36,0:47:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we held back\Nfor several years.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.36,0:47:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nwe held back
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.36,0:47:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the publication.\NMost of,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.40,0:47:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nthe recent news,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.40,0:47:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we knew years ago.\NWe knew years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.40,0:47:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,food for oil\Nand all that kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.40,0:47:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew that years ago.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.40,0:47:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it allows you\Naccess to information.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.50,0:47:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nnot all the information
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.50,0:48:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,can you share\Nwith the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.50,0:48:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.50,0:48:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a great deal\Nwe did not share
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.50,0:48:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with the world.\NAnd,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.50,0:48:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's bad enough\Nin blogger land
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.50,0:48:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with what we did,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.59,0:48:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't\Nsay,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.59,0:48:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,tell everything,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.59,0:48:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nall right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.71,0:48:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthe,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.71,0:48:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,if the intention\Nis integrous then,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.71,0:48:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,this serves\Na very useful
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.71,0:48:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pragmatic function.\NThis is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.71,0:48:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the perennial philosophy.\NAlthough,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.71,0:48:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's actually,\NI mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.71,0:48:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the,\Nthis is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.92,0:48:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the perennial\Nphilosophy
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.92,0:48:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.\NIt's most recent,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.80,0:48:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a psychologist\Nnamed,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.80,0:48:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,something,\Nwho published
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.80,0:48:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,an article\Non it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.80,0:48:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the 50s.\NColumbia
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.80,0:48:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychoanalytic\NInstitute
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.94,0:48:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,where I,\Nmy analyst was.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.94,0:48:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were\Nour training
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.94,0:48:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,analysts there.\NThese are called
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.00,0:48:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the\NPsychoanalytic
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.00,0:48:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Institute.\NThese are called
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.00,0:48:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the\NEmergency Emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.00,0:49:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,These are called\Nthe Welfare Emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.00,0:49:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And,\Nthey taught
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.00,0:49:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a tech,\Na variation
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.00,0:49:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of Freudian\Npsychoanalysis
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.00,0:49:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,called\NAdaptational.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.00,0:49:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Adaptational Analysis.\NHow do any
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.00,0:49:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of these\Nserve
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.00,0:49:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,adaptation?\NWe can see
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.00,0:49:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the lower ones\Ndo not serve
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.00,0:49:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,adaptation\Nvery well.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.44,0:49:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.44,0:49:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll move on.\NThese are
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.53,0:49:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all logarithmic\Nnumbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.53,0:49:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The distribution\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.53,0:49:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind.\NApproximately
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.53,0:49:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,80%\Nof mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.92,0:49:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is below\N200.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.21,0:49:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe'll move on
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.21,0:49:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next.\NThis is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.19,0:49:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.19,0:49:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,against time.\NAnd,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.65,0:49:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll move on.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.65,0:49:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you see\Nmankind's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.65,0:49:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,level of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.01,0:49:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is rising\Nrapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.01,0:49:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Ntherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.38,0:50:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it's rational\Nto be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.38,0:50:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,optimistic.\NThe other thing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.38,0:50:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is that\Neverything,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.44,0:50:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,everything\Nand anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.51,0:50:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up\Nwith a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.51,0:50:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,self-verifying\Nconcordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.51,0:50:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is\Nso,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.51,0:50:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,then this\Nshould be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.51,0:50:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so,\Ntoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.51,0:50:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Neven if
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.51,0:50:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology\Nisn't right,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.51,0:50:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it's probably\Nthe most useful
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.51,0:50:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,fraud in\Nhistory.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.09,0:50:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If it works,\Nthey'll knock
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.73,0:50:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it,\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.73,0:50:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what I\Nmean?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.73,0:50:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we can\Nmake a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.73,0:50:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,huge\Ninvestment
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.73,0:50:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,such as\Nthe epics
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.73,0:50:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of the\Nearth
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.73,0:50:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,over great\Ntime,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.73,0:50:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,three and a\Nhalf billion
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.96,0:50:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,years ago.\NThree and a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.96,0:50:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,half billion\Nyears ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.96,0:50:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nwe can track
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.19,0:50:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution\Nof life
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.19,0:51:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,over\Nthe epics
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.19,0:51:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of billions\Nof years
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.19,0:51:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrate\Nwhat was the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.19,0:51:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,energy of\Nlife
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.19,0:51:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when it\Nfirst
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.19,0:51:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared.\NThat's
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.19,0:51:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,very interesting.\NGoing into
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.23,0:51:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution\Nof this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.23,0:51:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,planet\Nover great
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.36,0:51:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,periods of\Ntime,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.36,0:51:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,three and a\Nhalf billion
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.51,0:51:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,years or\Nsomething like
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.51,0:51:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\NOkay,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.51,0:51:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so,\Nand then how
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.51,0:51:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,oxygen arose,\Nchlorophyll,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.51,0:51:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.\NThere wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.51,0:51:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,any oxygen\Nhere until
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.51,0:51:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the chlorophyll\Ncritters got
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.51,0:51:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,here,\Nthe vegetation,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.51,0:51:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which of\Ncourse takes
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.61,0:51:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the carbon for\Nthe forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.61,0:51:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the Amazon forest\Nputs out.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.61,0:51:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what\Npercent of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.61,0:51:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the earth's\Noxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.61,0:51:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so,\Nwe'll move on
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.71,0:51:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next\Nslide.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.19,0:51:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\NEcclesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.19,0:51:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we can track\Nthe evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.19,0:51:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of life,\Nit's a
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.19,0:52:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nlevel from
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.19,0:52:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the very\Nbeginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.19,0:52:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NThen we can track
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.19,0:52:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it through\Nthe animal
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.19,0:52:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,kingdom.\NWe can track
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.19,0:52:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it through\Nthe animal
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.19,0:52:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,kingdom because\Nbirds are in
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.19,0:52:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there about\Nsomeplace,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.19,0:52:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,birds.\NBirds,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.11,0:52:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah,\Nare less than
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.11,0:52:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,200.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.11,0:52:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with the exception\Nof birds,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.11,0:52:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200\Nis primarily
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.11,0:52:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,from a\Nhuman view
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.11,0:52:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,predatory.\NOf course,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.21,0:52:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from the animal's\Nview,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.21,0:52:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he's not\Npredatory,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.44,0:52:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he's just\Nhaving lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.44,0:52:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't\Nhave lunch
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.44,0:52:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you\Nbite it hard
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.44,0:52:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it\Ngets delicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.46,0:52:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,huh?\NThe same
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.46,0:52:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,energy field\Nin a human
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.46,0:52:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is usually\Naccompanied
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.46,0:52:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by,\Nor due
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.76,0:52:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to other\Nthings.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.76,0:52:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Also,\Nplease do not
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.78,0:52:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,ask me\Nwhy,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.78,0:52:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,send me\Nan email
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.78,0:52:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,why dolphins\Ncalibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.78,0:53:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,less,\Nmore than
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.30,0:53:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,whales.\NPlease do
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.30,0:53:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,not.\NI don't
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.40,0:53:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know why\Nthe hell
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.40,0:53:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they do\Nthat.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.40,0:53:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just\Nthe way
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.76,0:53:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it is.\NAll right,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.76,0:53:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so we go\Nthrough the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.76,0:53:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,animal kingdom.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.76,0:53:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Nthe usefulness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.76,0:53:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the\Nfraudulent
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.76,0:53:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,technique\Nin the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.76,0:53:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology,\Nit lays
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.76,0:53:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,out a\Nwhole
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.76,0:53:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary\Nmap of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.80,0:53:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire\Nanimal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.80,0:53:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only of\Nlife from
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.80,0:53:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,when it\Nfirst appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.80,0:53:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,on earth,\Nbut through
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.80,0:53:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole\Nanimal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.80,0:53:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,\Nwe're
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.94,0:53:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,going to\Nlook at
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.03,0:53:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution\Nof the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.25,0:53:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,ego.\NI think
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.25,0:53:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,medieval\NChristianity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.25,0:53:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,had a\Ndownside
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.80,0:54:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that tends\Nto
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.80,0:54:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,result in\Naversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.80,0:54:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's\Nlooking at
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.80,0:54:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,lower levels\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.88,0:54:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as sin,\Nsackcloth,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.88,0:54:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ashes,\Npenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.36,0:54:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets\Nsort of a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.36,0:54:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,dismal\Ndownness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.36,0:54:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to it\Nin the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.36,0:54:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ego.\NAnd here
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.36,0:54:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it is.\NHere's the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.36,0:54:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ego,\Nhow it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.36,0:54:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved\Nthrough the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.36,0:54:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,animal kingdom\Nover periods
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.36,0:54:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of time.\NSo that we
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.36,0:54:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,re-contextualize\Nthe ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.07,0:54:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not as\Nsin and
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.07,0:54:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,evil\Nrequiring
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.28,0:54:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,penance,\Nguilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.28,0:54:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,self-hatred,\Nand even
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.28,0:54:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,self-destruction\Nout of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.55,0:54:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,On the\Ncontrary,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.96,0:54:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's\Nour
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.96,0:54:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,ego.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.03,0:54:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when you\Nthink about
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.03,0:54:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nlocus
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.05,0:54:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of\Nevil,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.05,0:54:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't\Ncall all
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.09,0:55:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,these people\Nevil here,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.09,0:55:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,can you?\NYou can't
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.59,0:55:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,call all\Nthese people
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.59,0:55:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,evil,\Njust because
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.59,0:55:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they calibrate\Nbelow 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.59,0:55:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.59,0:55:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,hippopotamuses\Ncan be
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.59,0:55:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,quite kindly.\NThere was
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.80,0:55:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a wonderful\None on
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.80,0:55:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the History\Nis nursing the alligators.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.42,0:55:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's put in a good word for the hippopotamus.\NIt's a bad-looking thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.94,0:55:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They need somebody to speak for them.\NOkay, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.84,0:55:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we can take the kinesiologic test\Nand go through the entire intellectual history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.13,0:55:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We can go all the way back.\NOf course, the greatest time was the Golden Era in Greece,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.90,0:55:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and life has really gone downhill since then.\NLife was at its peak in Athens, in Greece,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.46,0:56:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in about 350, 400, 500 B.C.,\Nthe time of Socrates, Plato, Aristotle, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.51,0:56:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we can go through the great books of the Western world\Nand calibrate what is the intellectual background
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.86,0:56:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of understanding of the Western world.\NThis is the basis of all of the Western world,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.26,0:56:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we calibrate all the great names in history.\NAll the great names in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.96,0:56:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and...\NAnd this in itself serves as quite an interesting thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.03,0:56:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They say it would take 10 years to study the great books of the Western world.\NTake 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.90,0:56:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Takes 10 years, okay.\NVery interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.34,0:56:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice the limitation of the intellect.\NWe notice that Freud, Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.28,0:56:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated 499.\N499.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.67,0:56:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the 400s...\NThis is the world of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.07,0:57:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world of science.\NKant, Kepler, the great astronomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.15,0:57:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The great names in history here are all in the mid-400s.\NHippocrates at 485,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.15,0:57:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the discovery of the human...\NGalen...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.15,0:57:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton, 499.\N499 is about as high as you can get with the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.23,0:57:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 499, you have to leave the world of cause and effect,\Nthe Newtonian paradigm of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.23,0:57:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because 500 is the emergence of the non-linear.\NBelow 500 is the world of the linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.51,0:57:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which is provable, documentable, and provable.\NFrom 500 and up, suddenly reality jumps to the subjective,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.51,0:57:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,experiential, not provable, not logical,\Ncannot be documented, but transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.51,0:58:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, from 500 and up, our spiritual energies,\Ntherefore, people ask me,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.67,0:58:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the relationship between science and spirituality,\Nor science and theology?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.67,0:58:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell them, there isn't any.\NThere isn't any.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.98,0:58:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Two different realms altogether.\NThe 400s can talk about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.98,0:58:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can talk about it,\Nbut that's all they can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.98,0:58:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's intellectualization.\NYou can't prove the existence of God through the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.23,0:58:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I was once a rabid atheist,\Nand I remember St. Thomas Aquinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.23,0:58:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I had straight A in theology and everything and such,\Neven though I was an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.48,0:58:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Thomas Aquinas says,\Narguments, which he derived from Aristotle,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.48,0:58:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,arguments for the proof of the existence of God\Nare considered nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.13,0:58:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the argument for first cause.\NThat which is infinite has no beginning or ending,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.19,0:59:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so how could it have a cause?\NThe argument for first cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.19,0:59:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Friday afternoon,\Nwe go to the bar and, of course, argue about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.15,0:59:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it was fun being an atheist.\NI was a rabid atheist for some years.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.15,0:59:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already told you how I arrived there.\NSir Isaac Newton then is 499, Plato 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.57,0:59:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,See the great names throughout history,\NShakespeare, Spinoza.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.53,0:59:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And we always point out that, unfortunately,\NMarx got in, inadvertently put in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.53,0:59:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his historical importance.\NBut at 130, he brings this whole scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.53,0:59:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,all of them collectively,\Nwith Marx, comes to 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.63,0:59:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Without Marx, it comes to 465.\NTherefore, falsehood has a serious,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.63,0:59:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,deleterious effect on society,\Nand history of Marxism merely demonstrates that fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.63,0:59:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fallacy there was a projecting\Nduality of perpetrator-victim into the world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.63,1:00:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and politicizing it.\NOkay, so move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.63,1:00:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next.\NThis is the world, the linear, provable world,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.67,1:00:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which is content, content.\NBut the content occurs in an approximate field,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.67,1:00:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and that even in a greater context,\Nthe nonlinear context, the infinite context,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.67,1:00:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the absolute by which we calibrate\Nthe truth of anything here is in contrast to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.73,1:00:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The approximate field is local conditions.\NThings appear when local conditions,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.59,1:00:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when potentiality becomes an actuality,\Nwhen local conditions are favorable.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.01,1:00:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So the local conditions don't cause it.\NThey allow the potentiality to actualize.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.07,1:01:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The seed, when it gets sun and warmth and water,\Nits potential becomes an actual.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.21,1:01:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But the sun and the water does not cause it to do that.\NSo in appropriate circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.28,1:01:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this is called in logic, in ethics itself,\Nsituational ethics,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.28,1:01:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which some religions don't like\Nbecause they think it can be used as a cop-out excuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.53,1:01:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But the law recognizes that the degree of guilt, etc.,\Ndepends on the conditions at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.63,1:01:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And insanity, defense, all these things take that into account.\NNow, from our own research,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.69,1:01:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we come to the discovery\Nthat even without culpability,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.17,1:01:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you are still responsible and accountable.\NThe act, you are still accountable and responsible karmically,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.09,1:01:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you may have very little culpability\Ndue to other factors.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.19,1:02:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to differentiate between culpability\Nand accountability and responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.34,1:02:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough of that.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.65,1:02:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That which attracts, this is called lower mind,\Nis less evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.65,1:02:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's less evolved.\NThat mind, for instance, cannot really comprehend kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.28,1:02:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness 160 is unable to comprehend it.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.28,1:02:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it projects its own limitation onto what's out there\Nand thinks it sees it as out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.28,1:02:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, it doesn't work unless the people involved\Nreach consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.36,1:02:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,200.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.36,1:02:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because otherwise it's dominated by lower mind,\Nwhich hangs out around 155,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.36,1:03:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the level of skepticism and all that, about 160.\NIt's unable to comprehend.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.48,1:03:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to move over 200 towards higher mind.\NHigher mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.73,1:03:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have the capacity for faith,\Nthe integrity with which a thing is spoken,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.00,1:03:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the integrity.\NYou have to sense it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.00,1:03:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can sense the integrity.\NYou can't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.09,1:03:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NMeaning it's a person that has no particular personal gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.09,1:03:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any difference whether it goes this way or that way.\NThat level of consciousness is called neutral.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.44,1:03:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With neutral, if you get this job,\Nif you don't get this job, you'll get another.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.44,1:03:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the big deal?\NYou're not going to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.82,1:03:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Easygoing.\NThese people are very positionalized and emotionalized, everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.34,1:03:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalized.\NYesterday's paper, the Arizona Republic,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.34,1:04:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,said in an article that people voted for a certain proposition\Nprimarily with their emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.34,1:04:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's scary, isn't it?\NNot because they reason what's best for the country,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.11,1:04:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what's fair, what's equitable,\Njust from emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.11,1:04:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just emotion.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.11,1:04:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So 155 is emotionalism without thought.\NIt doesn't mean sensitivity, et cetera, or balance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.11,1:04:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So move to the next.\NThis is just to show, again,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.80,1:04:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we're trying to show a bridge between the Newtonian linear limitation\Nand the nonlinear, which is the spiritual domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.80,1:04:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics is, again, only a pedagogical technique.\NIt doesn't prove anything that we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.80,1:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But it does provide a means of comprehending\Nwhy prayer is a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.80,1:04:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's effective.\NThis has to do with wave and particle and potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.82,1:05:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that potentiality becomes an actuality\Nunder the appropriate conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.88,1:05:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What's one of the conditions?\NIntention.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.88,1:05:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention is the Heisenberg process is intention.\NSo a man sits with his feet on the desk,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.76,1:05:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,imagines building the biggest, tallest building in the world.\NThen it gathers energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.11,1:05:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he gets his banker friends behind it.\NHe talks to architects.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.11,1:05:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And in exactly one year, one year,\Nthe Empire State Building went up on, what is it,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.36,1:05:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,32nd Street or 32nd Street?\NOne year. One year.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.36,1:05:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to this, Native American steel workers,\Nwho were absolutely fearless of height,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.51,1:05:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,60 stories up walking on a beam.\NAnyway, they were fearless.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.51,1:05:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, it took the intention to make it happen.\NAnd that's Wayne Dyer's very popular book,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.51,1:06:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Power of Intention.\NIntention is what drives also all spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.51,1:06:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Your intention.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.07,1:06:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is explained extremely well.\NSo this is, let's say it's an analogy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.07,1:06:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not an explanation, not an explanation.\NIt's an analogy that by intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.59,1:06:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality becomes an actuality.\NThat is, the intention is part of the outer field,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.07,1:06:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of the field of context.\NOkay, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.07,1:06:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just, you get two different paradigms.\NThe proof, this is the world of provability.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.57,1:06:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is confirmable but not provable.\NYou can't prove you love somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.57,1:06:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove that you care about your dog.\NNo way to prove that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.55,1:07:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, this is limited and this is unlimited.\NWhen you, in context,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.48,1:07:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in contemplation and meditation,\Nyou try to move from this paradigm to this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.48,1:07:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to move from the specific linear restricted focused\Nto the nonlinear overall context,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.75,1:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the overall context.\NOkay, so we'll move over to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.76,1:07:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Linear gradations.\NYes, we said the mind thinks dualistically,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.65,1:07:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,good and bad,\Nblack and white,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.30,1:07:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,high and low,\Nhot and cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.30,1:07:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are positionalities.\NBecause people say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.30,1:07:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you mean a positionality?\NPositionality is an optional point of view.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.30,1:07:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist in the world.\NIt doesn't exist in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.55,1:07:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NSo I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.55,1:08:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,now, imagine three points here,\Na point here,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.88,1:08:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a point here,\Na point here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.88,1:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, now connect the dots.\NYou just made a triangle.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.00,1:08:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does the triangle exist?\NUp there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.92,1:08:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Constellations of astrology are from the viewpoint of the witness.\NIf you take a spaceship and go up there,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.56,1:08:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there ain't no Sagittarius up there.\NIt only looks like Sagittarius from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.56,1:08:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,From here, it looks like a dog.\NTherefore, they have no independent existence
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.65,1:08:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,except as a mentalization which you project into the world.\NThere is no constellation there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.78,1:08:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the universe.\NYou understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.78,1:08:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody don't get it?\NYou can take any bunch of dots,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.77,1:08:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a kid,\Nyou can make it into a horse or a dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.77,1:08:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's a projection.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.88,1:08:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the crux of what we teach has to do,\Nof course,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.13,1:09:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with the differentiation between res interna,\Nres cogitans,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.13,1:09:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and res externa,\Nthe world the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.28,1:09:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A very important distinction.\NVery important distinction.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.28,1:09:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Of Descartes.\NThe ordinary mind thinks that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.43,1:09:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,how it sees it is how it is.\NThat, of course, is the comment by Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.14,1:09:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That all men choose only what they perceive to be the good.\NIt's just that they don't know the real good from the false good.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.14,1:09:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But that does reinforce your understanding of the innocence of mankind.\NThat mankind can only know what's within
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.39,1:09:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,without some kind of a higher teaching.\NSo, we use temperature.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.72,1:09:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We say this is very hot.\NAnd I always say this is very cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.85,1:09:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That would...\NThere's only one variable,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.85,1:09:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of heat or the absence of heat.\NThere aren't two variables, heat and cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.85,1:10:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one.\NHeat is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.85,1:10:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's present, we say it's hot.\NIf it's not present, we say it's cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.85,1:10:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One variable, heat.\NWe do the same thing with the calibrated scale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.85,1:10:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One variable, called truth.\NIt's either present or not present, and to what degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.85,1:10:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Very simple, you know.\NCalibrating the laws of consciousness is very, very simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.85,1:10:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with goodness.\NLight.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.27,1:10:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He said there's two opposites, light and darkness.\NThere's either light or there's not light.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.15,1:10:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not two opposites.\NAnd the best example of all is on and off.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.35,1:10:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Offness is not the opposite of onness.\NYou can't send offness down an electric wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.25,1:10:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Electricity is either present or not present.\NOr it's not present.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.25,1:10:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't send offness.\NThe opposite doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.25,1:10:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a meditation, you understand.\NYou only send electricity there or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.25,1:11:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Electricity is either there or it ain't there.\NHeat is either there, light is either there.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.25,1:11:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And truth is either there or not.\NSo to what degree is truth there is the very purpose of calibrating levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.25,1:11:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be extremely there, very little there, hardly there at all.\NWhen you correlate that with all of human history and calibrate all the important figures, countries, books, movies, everything on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.27,1:11:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you come out with a configuration that even without kinesiology would make complete and total sense to anybody who's sane.\NMove over.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.01,1:11:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSpiritual practices, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.17,1:11:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, for the first time really,\Nyou can calibrate the relative truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.00,1:12:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the reality, the real authenticity of various things that are completely nonlinear and not provable.\NYou can't prove that the Lord's Prayer, you know, does any good in the world at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.00,1:12:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you prove it?\NYou can't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.00,1:12:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.03,1:12:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can certainly pick up the likelihood by calibrating it, calibrating it.\NThe Lord's Prayer is 650.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.60,1:12:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, om, pronounced correctly as oh, calibrates different than ah-oh-um.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.02,1:12:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah-oh-um.\NI say that because there's a translation by Satchitananda in which he does say A-U-M,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.40,1:12:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think it's incorrect.\NQuite a bit of difference versus a three-syllable version of it, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.56,1:13:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting to notice.\NOm Namah Shivaya.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.27,1:13:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all the great chants.\NAmmanipadmiham.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.59,1:13:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do an om for fun.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.11,1:13:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hold the people in the disaster, in the gopherry in mind and do om.\NHold them in mind and go om.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.10,1:13:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.76,1:13:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention is to bring them spiritual energy to uplift them, uplift them,\Nto pray to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.76,1:13:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,through periods of great stress\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.96,1:14:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,having been through periods of great stress myself\Nit's only by surrendering to God
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.61,1:14:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that you survive them\Nas they take off your leg or your thumb
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.22,1:14:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever they do to you\Nsurgery, no anesthesia, whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.78,1:14:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of war you're about to blow up\Nall you can do is surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.88,1:14:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,continuously in a prayerful\Nattitude
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.61,1:14:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrender to God\Nand once karmic proclivities will then
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.14,1:14:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,emerge of their own nature\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.13,1:14:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we know also from kinesiologic research\Nthat there's population
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.75,1:14:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,karma, population karma\Nwhole populations
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.55,1:14:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we here in this room\Nare part of a population wave
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.86,1:14:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,population waves\Neach population seems to
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.11,1:14:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,be subject to various things\NWorld War I, World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.47,1:14:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Crimean War, War of 1812\Nstarvation, drought
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.14,1:14:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,okay let's ask about that\Nthat's just intuitive
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.39,1:15:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask this\Nin the name of the highest good
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.42,1:15:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,there is such a thing as population karma\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.77,1:15:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,intuition\Nso a lot of things you intuit it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.84,1:15:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and it seems rather certain\Nand actually you know it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.86,1:15:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,actually you know it\Nbecause you've existed over a great period of time
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.28,1:15:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know it\Nbecause you lived through it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.06,1:15:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Num
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.48,1:15:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Num
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.77,1:15:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Num
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.90,1:15:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Num
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.53,1:15:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Num
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.60,1:15:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nso there is whole population
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.80,1:15:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic consequences\Nnot consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.23,1:15:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but opportunities\Nbecause it's really
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.02,1:15:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,only when you're faced with the sword\Nthat you make that decision
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.03,1:15:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrender my life to thee oh lord\Nunreservedly
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.06,1:15:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if you physically die\Nyou die
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.30,1:15:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nso if you die you die
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.39,1:15:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,big deal\NI remember I told you the incident
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.89,1:16:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,here's this mind sitting here\Nwith this horn sticking out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.71,1:16:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it's about this far from the ship you know\Nand this guy looks at me
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.34,1:16:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I said\Nyou go you go
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.26,1:16:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nbut you see how when you communicate that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.30,1:16:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender\Nhow it reinforces the other person
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.56,1:16:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because the fear left his eyes\Nhe looked at me and he got that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.02,1:16:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and he just\Nwent that way too
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.84,1:16:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as tough as it is\Nother than surrendering each step of the way
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.21,1:16:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't any other way\Nand you look at me and you say
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.48,1:16:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you learned what you can from it\Nand as I said
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.32,1:16:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,there is interestingly the survivors that we see\Nin storm stories almost all mention how they prayed to God
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.39,1:16:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the one that's most interesting\Na couple of people who got picked up
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.92,1:16:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in a tornado\Nand lifted
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.65,1:16:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,like a block up in the air\Nthere they are suspended a block up in the air
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.48,1:17:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of feet up in the air\Nin a state of profound peace over Canaan
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.23,1:17:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,several of them in a row I said\Nit was like an infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.93,1:17:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was held in infinite peace\NI was always sad
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.17,1:17:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when it was over\Nand I had to come
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.56,1:17:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,crashing back to earth\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.40,1:17:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that option to transcend the identification with the physicality\Nand realize the truth that you're a spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.18,1:17:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a great opportunity\Nman's catastrophe is
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.59,1:17:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,God's opportunity is the favorite saying about that isn't it\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.14,1:17:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by contemplation\Nand meditation is a different thing
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.47,1:17:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but by contemplation\Ninstead of identifying with form
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.47,1:17:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with content\Nemotionalizing it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.47,1:17:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,getting positionalized about it\Nand reactive to it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.47,1:17:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you become non-attached\Nyou become the observer witness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.47,1:18:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a contemplative lifestyle\Nyeah you know what's going on
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.10,1:18:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I got the gist of it all\Nhow many videos do I have to see of disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.10,1:18:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean I got it\NI got it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.14,1:18:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,total disaster in all of its expression\Nall of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.14,1:18:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you get it\Nwithout getting caught in it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.52,1:18:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,oh it's so sad\Noh it's so bad
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.52,1:18:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to emotionalize about it\Nbecause emotionalizing doesn't help anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.52,1:18:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,see\Nin the middle of a crisis
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.52,1:18:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need people that are blubbering and crying\Nyou need a cool head
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.61,1:18:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're on the verge of death\Nyou need to be cool
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.39,1:18:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're about to blow up\Nyou're second from disaster
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.42,1:18:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,second from disaster\Nyou just become very calm
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.44,1:18:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,alright\Nsuper calm
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.56,1:18:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and then\Nemotionalize about it later
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.81,1:18:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on TV or on a blog site\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.92,1:19:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.72,1:19:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so you\Na contemplative lifestyle then
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.72,1:19:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is an awareness\Nin which you open yourself to be
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.72,1:19:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,aware of the field\Nrather than the content of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.72,1:19:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the field tells you whether it's safe or not safe\Nthe field tells you what the overall intention is
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.44,1:19:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it's closer to intention\Nand non-verbal non-linear knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.77,1:19:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,like a knowingness comes forth\Nyes there is such a thing as population karma
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.77,1:19:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can go and verify it\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.77,1:19:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it just seemed like an awareness\Nbut it doesn't come out of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.77,1:19:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it just comes out of being with\Nthe overall situation
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.77,1:19:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,being with the overall situation\Nwe all send help in whatever linear form we can
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.72,1:19:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we all send checks and do what we can\Nin the linear domain
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.85,1:19:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but to the person who's laying there in the foxhole\Nlinear domain is
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.85,1:20:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,not all that interesting at the moment\Nbecause what's up
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.85,1:20:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're up against is spirit\Nyou're up against whether
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.85,1:20:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to\Nfeel
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.21,1:20:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,safe no matter what\Nbodies come and bodies go
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.78,1:20:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,your attitude is going to be the result of the context\Nso when we pray for people as we did
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.78,1:20:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we're trying to send spiritual energy to the context\Nso that somebody who is about ready to give up
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.78,1:20:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopeless\Nsuddenly feels
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.78,1:20:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,no I'll keep going\Nwhere did they get the oh I'll keep going
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.78,1:20:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they got it from being the upliftment\Nbecause as we hold them in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.78,1:20:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and do om or pray\Nwe uplift the field
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.78,1:20:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby everybody's upliftment\Nis uplifted in the field
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.14,1:20:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind evolves by the upliftment of the field\Nupliftment of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.80,1:21:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so we withdraw then to the watcher\Nthe witness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.80,1:21:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer the witness\Nand once
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.80,1:21:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you get in the habit of being the witness of the phenomena\Nthen over time
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.93,1:21:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,even the witness disappears\Nfor a time there is identifying with the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.93,1:21:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but pretty soon you realize the witness\Ndisappears
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.93,1:21:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and that comes about because witnessing is happening of its own\Nthere is no you that is doing the witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.06,1:21:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no this or that\Nthe witnessing is happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.06,1:21:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't any you doing a witnessing\Nso that gets you out of the duality of a separate me
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.14,1:21:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and of that\Nthe witnessing is happening of its own
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.07,1:21:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it always is\Nthe other way the last lecture was supposed to be on
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.52,1:21:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,equanimity or something wasn't it\Nyes
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.43,1:22:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we forgot to mention it anyway\Nso equanimity then comes from non-attachment
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.19,1:22:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,detachment\Nyou become the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.19,1:22:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and being the witness you have no positionality about\Nwhat is going on
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.19,1:22:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you have no positionality\Nso you are detached
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.28,1:22:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and pretty soon the observer witness goes away\Nand what is
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.60,1:22:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the only thing left is consciousness itself\Nconsciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.09,1:22:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,without a subject and an object\Na non-dualistic way of being
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.76,1:22:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore contemplative lifestyle\Neventuates
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.34,1:22:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,into a non-linear non-dualistic way of being\Nway of being
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.47,1:22:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and your way of being then\Nis in a greater accord with reality than it is with content
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.68,1:23:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're the witness you get the total same\Nyou don't have to hear somebody blubbering
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.19,1:23:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we need help here\Nright
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.44,1:23:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,ten thousand people in disaster\Nit's like saying isn't that a beautiful sunset
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.27,1:23:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you know the way to kill a sunset is\Neverybody is getting off on a sunset
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.27,1:23:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody says isn't that a beautiful sunset\Nunnecessary protrusion
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.27,1:23:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or isn't that beautiful music\Nit was so you spoke yes
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.26,1:23:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the contemplative person gets it\Nwhen we were in Europe you know
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.60,1:23:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrating the Greek cathedrals\Nit was really astonishing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.60,1:23:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd walk into this incredible cathedral\Nincredible sculpture
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.60,1:23:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see even one cornice\Nit took a man's entire lifetime to dedicate
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.60,1:24:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because all the workmen are dedicating their efforts to God\Nhere's this incredible
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.71,1:24:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been there a thousand years\Nin England the one I first spoke at in 71
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.43,1:24:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been there a thousand years\NI can't think of the name of it at the moment
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.43,1:24:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah right yes\Nyeah anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.27,1:24:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so here you are in these incredible cathedrals\Nand people are running around with their cell phones
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.27,1:24:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,talking to their mother\Nordering merchandise
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.27,1:24:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it's like studying you see\NI can't believe it
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.27,1:24:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sort of annoyed\Nthat happened also in France
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.36,1:24:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in Chartres I think it was yeah\Nand I thought you know
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.63,1:24:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,where are the people running this cathedral you know\NI mean I would be telling them
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.63,1:24:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,shush or get out\Nyou know what I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.63,1:24:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah but I guess this is the era of self-expression\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.88,1:24:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,self-expression\Ntalking on your cell phone
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.88,1:25:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nunbelievable right
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.88,1:25:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like missing the entire context\Nso caught up in this personal
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.88,1:25:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,self-interest content\Nthat they don't even get
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.92,1:25:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what it's about\Nsame thing happened in the Lincoln Memorial in Washington DC
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.92,1:25:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it always makes you speechless\Nthe experience
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.92,1:25:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not like a picture of it\Nthe experience of it is just stunning overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.92,1:25:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity you're just confronted with\Nintegrity do or die kind of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.52,1:25:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is there\Ngrandeur the grandeur of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.52,1:25:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nand there again people were you know
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.77,1:25:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,on their cell phones\Nso we're gonna take a break
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.15,1:25:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,did you enjoy the little brief thing with kinesiology\NI don't know I thought it's
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.15,1:26:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we've never done it you know\Nbecause we're not teaching kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.64,1:26:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm not trying to convince anybody\Nand I have no vested interest
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.64,1:26:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in owning any kinesiology\Nthings you know
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.64,1:26:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you want to ignore it\Nthe truth is exactly the same
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.92,1:26:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,without the calibrations\Nthe truth is exactly the same
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.14,1:26:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the calibration does\Nis give you a verification from the linear domain
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.14,1:26:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can remain a modern human\Nthinking
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.14,1:26:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,who's used to logic and proof and all that kind of thing\Nand move with comfort and ease into the non
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.14,1:26:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,linear non-provable\Nsubjective experiential
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.14,1:26:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nso we'll meet again after
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.06,1:26:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,11.30\N11.30
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.31,1:27:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,okay\Nwe were talking about serenity
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.64,1:27:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,equanimity\Nin the last lecture
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.38,1:27:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I\Nthere was
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.38,1:27:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,one important thing I\Nforgot although I've spoken of it many times
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.50,1:27:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the contemplative state also it facilitates\Nbeing with the silent space
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.68,1:27:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which thinkingness arises\Nnow
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.68,1:27:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this can be discovered\Nin meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.23,1:27:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it also occurs of its own\Nvia contemplation
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.27,1:27:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm\Npresumes that thoughts are linear
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.48,1:27:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nit's being caused by this that or the other thing
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.48,1:28:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and it goes off into\Nnever never land
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.15,1:28:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,once the mind starts thinking\Nit's unstoppable
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.15,1:28:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore to try and look\Nyou can't find
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.43,1:28:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a peace between two thoughts\Nand we've said this before
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.43,1:28:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the mistranslations of the Buddha\Nhas to do with that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.92,1:28:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite space is not between two thoughts\Nthe infinite space is prior to thought
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.14,1:28:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,okay let's see if that's correct\Nthe statement
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.76,1:28:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,if we have permission\Nis correct oh lord
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.76,1:28:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,yes\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.76,1:28:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as we can see\Nexperientially you'll notice
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.76,1:28:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if you watch thoughts\Nthey start out as sort of a vague urge
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.10,1:28:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,like dogginess arises\Nand then it becomes dog
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.39,1:28:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,then it becomes rover\Nand then it goes into how rover was run over
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.39,1:29:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and then how we all cried\Nyou know it's a whole long story
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.96,1:29:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in meditation with one pointedness of mind\Nyou witness the emergence of thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.11,1:29:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and you surrender them\Nat their point of origination
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.27,1:29:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,now in the beginning\Nyou decide that you can let go
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.27,1:29:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the sad story of how rover got run over\Nand how the children cried
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.27,1:29:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that crap\Nyou can let all that emotion out of you
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.27,1:29:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we know it was tragic\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.88,1:29:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already thought that sad tragic thought\Nprobably four or five hundred times
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.88,1:29:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not exactly news\Nokay
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.61,1:29:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll notice\Nthat one is enamored of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.19,1:29:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that the experience or edge of the ego\Nsurvives on thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.56,1:29:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it gets desperate\Nwhen there's nothing going on
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.56,1:30:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and it resorts to thinkingness to stay alive\Nbecause the ego has no source of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.15,1:30:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,other than animal energy\Nit doesn't have spiritual energy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.39,1:30:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual energy doesn't arrive\Ntill consciousness level 200
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.73,1:30:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so it seeks\Nsome kind of gain
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.22,1:30:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience or edge of the ego\Nis always out there
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.22,1:30:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,milking everything\Nfor what kind of juice it can get out of
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.22,1:30:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,tragedy\Noh poor old rover
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.22,1:30:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,oh\Noh the worst of the story
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.18,1:30:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,before the ego thrives\Noh my god
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.18,1:30:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the ultimate tragedy\Nand the steers start
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.39,1:30:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how the ego feeds itself\Nit juices it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.39,1:30:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't want to let it go\Nthat's the obstacle
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.39,1:30:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is the\Nego is getting such juice
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.39,1:30:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,out of negativity\Nthat it clings to it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.39,1:31:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the egotistic display\Nyou gotta get on the blog site
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.51,1:31:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell the world what you think about it\Nthe world's been waiting for it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.07,1:31:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all these centuries\Nit's funny
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.27,1:31:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway\Nalright
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.64,1:31:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so you're willing to give up the self indulgence\Nof thinking this
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.64,1:31:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the juice that you're getting out of all the drama\Nthe fear
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.88,1:31:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting juice out of the fear of the future\Nyou're getting juice out of clinging and grief out of the past
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.88,1:31:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the obstacles\Nthe primary obstacle
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.97,1:31:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is the juice that you're getting out of the experience or edge\Nalright
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.97,1:31:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you walk away from it\Nis you have to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.44,1:31:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to first see\Nthat all the ego's positionalities
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.44,1:31:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are devices to\Njuice energy out of them
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.44,1:31:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,out of being right\Ngetting even
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.44,1:32:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,being richer\Nmore famous
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.44,1:32:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,more\Nbeing right
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.44,1:32:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,getting even\Nholding a grudge
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.69,1:32:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,people will hold a grudge an entire lifetime\Nentire lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.21,1:32:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the diet aids\Nwhatever
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.21,1:32:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the same grudge they've had all these years\Noh god
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.27,1:32:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nyeah I remember that
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.46,1:32:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah I remember that\Nafter the world war two
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.46,1:32:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you know after the war was over\Nalmost instantly both sides forgave each other
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.97,1:32:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,almost instantly\Nfreaking war is over
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.68,1:32:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nso you salute the kamikaze pilots
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.68,1:32:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean they did what they could for their country\Nwith their white thing going
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.68,1:32:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and their bravery\Nand their courage
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.68,1:32:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and both sides respect each other\Neverything is fine
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.68,1:32:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they even celebrate together\Nsome members of the opposite sides became lifetime friends
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.85,1:33:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote books about it\Nand some people hung on to it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.10,1:33:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a veteran on TV not long ago\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.10,1:33:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\N50 years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.35,1:33:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's still hanging on to it\Nhe still hates them
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.35,1:33:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,50 years ago\Nwe were all forgiving each other
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.55,1:33:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody was doing what they had to do at the time\Nfor god
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.80,1:33:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for country\Nfor the Fuhrer
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.80,1:33:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you thought you were supposed to do\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.80,1:33:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan and the Hirohito was\Nthe sun god
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.80,1:33:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,descendant of the sun god\Nso you did it for god
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.80,1:33:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so each one does what he sees as the good\Nnow the experiencer
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.14,1:33:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is the advancing edge of the ego\Nand it is the processor
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.32,1:33:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer processes everything\Nit processes it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.46,1:33:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten thousandths of a second\Nafter the event
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.64,1:33:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore\Nyou never experience anything
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.64,1:34:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience the ego itself\Nthere's a readout of it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.40,1:34:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have permission to ask this oh lord\Nwhat I just spoke was the absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.82,1:34:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute truth oh lord\Namen
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.69,1:34:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,resist\Nthe absolute truth as far as we can verify
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.69,1:34:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see what I did with kinesiology\NI just want to verify it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.69,1:34:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a new thought\Nnever even heard of it expressed before
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.85,1:34:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never heard it expressed before\Nanyway
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.61,1:34:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this experiencer is out there\Nto juice things
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.81,1:34:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and it\Nso what's coming out of this
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.80,1:34:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is then the readout\Nso what you think is experiencing out there-ness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.89,1:34:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is not out there-ness\Nit's the ego's readout of out there-ness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.89,1:35:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it is so fast\None ten thousandths of a second
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.31,1:35:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that you cannot catch it\Nthe reason you can't
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.85,1:35:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,glimpse an infinite space between two thoughts\Nis that which the perceiver
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.72,1:35:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is moving at the same rate as the thoughts\Nyou see
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.72,1:35:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have to move faster than one ten thousandths of a second to catch it\Nwell the mind can't move faster
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.47,1:35:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,move that fast\Nso to use the mind to try and find an empty space
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.47,1:35:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,between two thoughts\Ndoesn't work
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.27,1:35:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know of anybody who became enlightened\Nby noting the space between two thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.27,1:35:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by certain meditative techniques\Nyou can hit a momentary saturity
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.17,1:35:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't last\Nand when you get up and open your eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.17,1:36:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer takes hold again\Nin the enlightened state then
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.64,1:36:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at a certain level of consciousness\Nwhat happens is the experiencer dissolves
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.64,1:36:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and then\Nthe brilliance and radiance
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.93,1:36:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity as all of existence shines forth\Nand stuns the mind silent
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.22,1:36:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's possible then to let go of the\Ndesire to think earlier and earlier in the game
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.82,1:36:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel the dogginess coming up\Nand you surrender it as it arises
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.07,1:36:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you follow the emergence of the thought\Neventually you come to the realization
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.18,1:36:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's an energy of thinkingness\Nthere's an energy that's creating this endless stream of thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.52,1:37:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and beneath that\Nif you surrender that
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.92,1:37:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinite silence\Nninety-nine percent of the mind is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.00,1:37:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to find the silence space\Nis not between thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.86,1:37:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but a priori\Nso it's like the sea
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.06,1:37:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've given the analogy of the flying fish coming out of the sea\Nthere's a still sea
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.25,1:37:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which the thoughts are arising individually\Nit's not very difficult
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.10,1:37:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact you can even do it while I'm talking\Nand I'm going to do the same thing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.27,1:37:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,beneath the field of thinkingness\Nthere is infinite silence
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.72,1:37:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the infinite silence\NI hear the doc talking about what he's talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.72,1:37:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no relationship to him\NI'm not interested in him
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.72,1:38:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly I don't even care what he's talking about\Nthe infinite silence space is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.53,1:38:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is the next step from contemplation\Nsee with contemplation you're not wanting to do anything
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.34,1:38:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to what's happening out there\Nyou don't have to rescue this person
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.34,1:38:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to challenge him\Nyou don't have to challenge this person
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.34,1:38:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to thump this person's chest\Neverything is just being what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.50,1:38:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,being what it is\Nwhat does the thing mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.72,1:38:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you exactly what everything means\Nwhat it means is what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.72,1:38:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what it means is what it is\Nidentity is its meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.61,1:38:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that saves you all kinds of cerebration\Nwhat does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.35,1:38:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it means what it is\NI told you the analogy of the cat
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.82,1:38:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you ask the cat\Nyou're telling a cat about being a cat
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.94,1:39:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cat says what does cat mean?\Nyou get down to the encyclopedia and the dictionary
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.10,1:39:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and you read them all what it says about cat\Nand the cat says that's got nothing to do with me
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.26,1:39:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's your head talking\Nwhat's that got to do with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.76,1:39:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say to the cat\Nwell then who are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.78,1:39:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the cat says I'm me\NI'm me that's what the cat is
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.81,1:39:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reality is subjectivity\Nthe cat doesn't know anything about catness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.03,1:39:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all\Nmentalization
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.03,1:39:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so the only reality is that of existence\Nof being that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.64,1:39:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore the enlightened state is merely to surrender\Neverything that is not the self with a capital S
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.64,1:40:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and one automatically is left with what one is\Nso enlightenment is not the attainment of something new
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.35,1:40:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the relinquishment of everything that stands in the way\Nthe surrender of everything
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.35,1:40:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so to understand the mechanisms of the ego and how it works\Nputs you at a tremendous advantage
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.35,1:40:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to undo every negative thing you could ever think about\Nor every experience you've ever had etc
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.40,1:40:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to merely witness\Nso from the contemplative style
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.89,1:40:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you become the witness\Nyou become the witness of how the experience is
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.89,1:40:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience your edge\Nis out there trying to juice things
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.89,1:40:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and a true renunciate\Nthen renounces that payoff of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.89,1:40:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,denies it reality\Nyou don't have to wear sackcloth and ashes
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.21,1:40:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to live on figs and nuts\Nand other disgusting diets
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.21,1:40:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to wear sandals\Nyou don't have to shave your head
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.77,1:41:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and retreat to a cave\Nnot necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.81,1:41:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you do it by intention now\Njust let go of the whole audience
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.47,1:41:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't care less what the audience thinks, feels\Nwhether they learned anything
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.68,1:41:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm completely and totally indifferent to it\NI couldn't care less
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.52,1:41:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that took one instant\Nsee, I didn't have to undress, wear sandals
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.44,1:41:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,go someplace\Nand eat weird things for 30 years
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.44,1:41:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that's an inner decision\Nto let go of the payoff
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.18,1:41:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the satisfaction, oh the audience is pleased\Nor the fear the audience is not pleased
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.18,1:41:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or gee I might be boring them\Nor oh oh I might be repeating myself
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.18,1:41:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or you know what I'm saying\Nthat would screw up your head totally
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.53,1:41:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you even talking about\Nit's got my head screwed up
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.53,1:41:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,golly I wonder if they are happy\Nwith what I'm talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.31,1:41:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,oh poor old rover\NI remember how he got run over
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.52,1:42:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,poor old rover\NI guess I gotta quit juicing fear
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.00,1:42:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,okay\Ncould you let go and please everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.00,1:42:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yep\Nhow long would it take you?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.00,1:42:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,done\Nalright so the easiest way into it
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.43,1:42:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is a contemplative lifestyle\Nin which you are only being that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.30,1:42:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is required\Nthere's no this or that
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.39,1:42:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,everything happens spontaneously\Nand as you retreat from the juice
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.03,1:42:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinking this then\Nyou let go wanting to think
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.44,1:42:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,could you surrender wanting to think\Nwould you be willing to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.44,1:42:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,your thinkingness to God?\NI surrender this thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.71,1:42:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to thee oh Lord\Nuh huh
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.18,1:42:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you step back into the silence\Nand you live in the silence
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.18,1:43:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the noise goes on\Nthe world goes on
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.69,1:43:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the bombs go off\Nthe buses collide
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.69,1:43:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's all out there\Nso that's what Ramana Maharshi means
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.97,1:43:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the world you think you see\Ndoesn't even exist yet
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.35,1:43:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that's true if you're at consciousness level\Nat 720
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.38,1:43:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're not I wouldn't walk across the street\Nwith your eyes closed
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.51,1:43:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing about spiritual truth is\Nyou have to be
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.51,1:43:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous\Nto the level that you're at
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.51,1:43:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it sounds good\Nyou know that the world you see is
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.72,1:43:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's at 720 or so\Nsee
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.72,1:43:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's true\Nthat's true if you're at 720
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.76,1:43:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not true if the sheriff is\Nat your door
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.28,1:44:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so the way to serenity then\Nis to
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.98,1:44:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,witness\Nby witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.98,1:44:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you get that the experiencer is out there\Njuicing everything
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.98,1:44:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,now we saw how the ego arose\Nover great periods of time
